			<h3>Bad Breath</h3>
			<p>
				Bad breath or halitosis is breath with an unpleasant odor.  Some bad breath, such as “morning mouth” or food (i.e. onion or garlic) tainted breath is normal.  However, bad breath may be caused by abnormal conditions that threaten your health and require diagnosis and treatment:
			</p>
			<%= image_tag 'wisdomtooth.jpg', :class => "float-right" %>	
			<ul>
				<li>Poor dental hygiene</li>
				<li>Infections in the mouth</li>
				<li>Dry Mouth (Xerostomia)</li>
				<li>Respiratory tract infections</li>
				<li>Diseases of the liver, lung, kidney, digestive trace,and sinus; diabetes, reflux, etc.</li>
				<li>Smoking and chewing tobacco</li>
			</ul>
			<p>	
				To establish its cause, we will review your medical history, diet, personal habits, and symptoms.  We also will carefully examine your teeth, gums, mouth, and salivary glands.  We then will provide you with appropriate treatment or refer you to a physician for further testing.<br>
			</p>
